  "texts": [
    "For each embedding e i, we compute three vectors: a query q i, a key k i and a value v i, using learned weight matrices W 𝛗, W k and W v:",
    "The attention score between token i and token j is calculated using the scaled dot-product of their queries and keys:",
    "• q i ⋅ k t v denotes the dot product of q i and the transpose of k v.",
    "• d k is the dimensionality of the key vectors.",
    "• The division by √ d k scales the dot products to prevent large values that could result in small gradients during training."
  ],
